Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Recommends: 7zip | p7zip-full
Description: hex editor, viewer and binary analyzer
 HexWalk is a Qt-based hex editor, viewer and binary analyzer aimed at
 reverse engineering and firmware analysis. Features include:
  * Advanced search across HEX, UTF-8, UTF-16 and regular expressions
  * Built-in binary signature scanner and extractor (HexDig)
  * Disassembler view powered by Capstone
  * Entropy chart and byte map visualisations
  * Hash calculator and bin/dec/hex converter
  * Diff view between two files
  * Byte-pattern tagging for parsing custom headers
 .
 The 7zip (or legacy p7zip-full) package is recommended to enable the
 archive extraction features of the embedded HexDig scanner.
